            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">The way to avoid telemarketers: by a former telemarketer.. Never sign up for anything where you will use your full name, city you live in and/or your address and/or your phone number. They can and will find you. <br />
<br />
Never sign up for anyhting in the mall. No free cars, surveys, free anything. Those are telemarketers fruit baskets.<br />
<br />
Ask to be put on the DNC list. If you return a call from your caller ID or answering service and wish to be put on the DNC list include your first and last name with your telephone number. If they call back you can sue them. If you fail to provide this information when returning their call you will not be taken off of the list.<br />
<br />
Ask to be put on the DNC list if you answer the phone. If it is a recording and you seriously want on the DNC list wait until someone answers the line.. Then ask. <br />
<br />
<br />
Telemarketers do hate their jobs. Unfortunatly they do pay them decently well and it pays the rent and puts food on the table for them. No reason being an ass to them unless they are an ass first.</font></p>
             
