              <tr>
                <td><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"> <font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1"><b>If you get a lot of telemarketing by the same company</b></font></td>
                <td align="right" nowrap>&laquo; 12-09-2002 05:20 PM &raquo;</td>
              </tr>
            </table>
             </font> 
            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">We had a problem with a local paper that would call us just about weekly while in Ohio. One of our friends was a manager in a telemarketing firm & actually told us the correct legal way to handle it.<br />
<br />
Keep a notepad by the phone. Write down the date, time, company name, employee name & extension. Tell that person specifically  to remove you from their calling list & never call back again.<br />
<br />
If they call back again, once again write down their information & ask to speak to a manager and/or supervisor. Write down that persons info & inform them that you have previous spoken to (give info you previously wrote down) & ask them once again to never call you back or you will pursue legal action.<br />
<br />
They do it again, write down the persons name & number & go find a lawyer. You have a legal case now to sue for harrassment.</font></p>
             
