            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">Some states do have a statwide DNC list. I can't think of any specifically now because its the end of the day and I'm a bit fried.  But all companies who do Telemarketing in that state are required to scrub customers against that list.  I'm thinking this may become the norm in the future for many states.<br />
<br />
As someone who has worked for and with Telemarkers for a long time now, I can definately appreciate that they can be annoying.  But the vast majority are legitmate business and people just trying to make a living.  And its also a pretty good way of contacting your customers if you have an existing relationship with them.  (response rates from mail are generally much lower than contact rates from telemarketing)<br />
<br />
What I can't stand is when 20/20, or whoever, runs some story on these scumbag scam artists who take old people's money, and they call it Telemarketing.  Its not.  Its fraud, and thievery, and those people should be put in jail.  It gives all Telemarketers a bad name, and unfortunately much of the general public thinks that's what Telemarketing is all about.</font></p>
             
