            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">I was a telemarketer for over a year for one of the most corrupt companies out there. The owner would come in and tell us to lie to customers to push sales, he made us be as aggressive as possible. If you asked to be taken off our list, guess what, we'd be calling you back the next week.<br />
<br />
I was good at what I did, I made a ton of money. I could sell ice to eskimos, but eventually I couldn't take lying to people over and over. I just never went back.<br />
<br />
I had fun, though. I did enjoy the job. Here's the thing that will surprise you the most: I LOVED it when people gave me crap. It was something interesting, a break from the monotony. As soon as I would hang up from someone tearing me a new one, I would laugh my ass off. Those were always the best calls.</font></p>
             
            <p></p>
            <p></p>
