            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">We have this new thing with our telephone company, Privacy Manager, that doesn't allow "out of area" calls to call my house.  When they do call from an actually number that shows up, it says, "Privacy Manager."  Meaning, someone is trying to sell, collect, or ask me to if i want a credit card.  When you answer it, it says, "you have a call, press 1 to find out who's calling."  You press 1 and it says, "Angela from Capital One is trying to get through.  If you want to accept push 1."  Which then I hang up!  <br />
<br />
Love it!!<br />
<br />
Ask your phone company about Privacy Manager.  Pretty soon I won't have any of them calling me!!</font></p>
             
